Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Brotherhood
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 37
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,===============================================================
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.35,0:01:39.87,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Who in the world are those guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.87,0:01:46.63,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,They're Kimblee's men, dispatched from the Central Army. Supposedly "bodyguards" for the Rockbell girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.80,0:01:51.25,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you planning to do at Briggs, Kimblee?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.12,0:01:58.84,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You should have told me if you were coming north.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.84,0:02:01.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have time. I was in a rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.93,0:02:05.14,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are {\i1}always{\i0\fscx30} {\r} in a rush!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.14,0:02:07.69,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Why were you locked up, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.69,0:02:09.44,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,It was just a misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.00,0:02:11.76,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be set free soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.28,0:02:14.73,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go through the formalities later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.36,0:02:17.19,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Mr. Kimblee.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.19,0:02:19.66,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Please look after these blockheads for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.25,0:02:21.37,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.81,0:02:29.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Don't trust Kimblee too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.30,0:02:31.81,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Why? He's a nice man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.87,0:02:38.51,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Rockbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.51,0:02:43.32,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Your parents were the doctors who lost their lives at Ishbal, were they not?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.80,0:02:45.79,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.79,0:02:46.77,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.93,0:02:52.16,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,It was my unit who recovered their bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.16,0:02:57.54,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,We were a second too late.\NWhen we arrived at the scene, they were already...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.33,0:02:59.53,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.34,0:03:06.02,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,They obeyed the ethics of medicine and\Nstuck to their convictions until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.02,0:03:07.96,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I admire them from the bottom of my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.97,0:03:11.43,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could have met them while they were still with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.00,0:03:21.55,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,They kept a picture that was taken with an adorable little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.16,0:03:25.45,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Your existence must have been what drove them onwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.97,0:03:32.91,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasure to make your acquaintance, Miss Winry Rockbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.24,0:03:38.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Do you know what he did at Ishbal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.38,0:03:49.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've only heard the true stories about Ishbal from the Lieutenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.74,0:03:52.50,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,From the Lieutenant...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.38,0:03:57.38,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,You're in love with Winry, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.81,0:04:10.01,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.01,0:04:13.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Just... Just think about something else, Ed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.56,0:04:16.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hydrogen, helium, lithium, beryllium...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.51,0:04:18.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...carbon, nitrogen, oxygen, sulfur...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.23,0:04:18.57,Default-alt,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,E-Ed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.99,0:04:22.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx95}...aluminum, silicon, phosphorus, chromium, manganese, iron...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.21,0:04:23.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...cobalt, nickel...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.63,0:04:27.07,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I fall for a weirdo like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.07,0:04:29.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.63,0:04:31.70,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.70,0:04:33.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oww!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.64,0:04:37.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,D-Damn you, I told you to let me know before you join the nerves!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.21,0:04:40.21,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, whatever. Now for your leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.47,0:04:48.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's so light!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.72,0:04:51.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't its durability suffer if you make it so light?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.05,0:04:56.31,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,If you look at the big picture, it's less durable than it used to be, but the key points have been reinforced.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.72,0:05:03.19,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you out of your cell?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.19,0:05:04.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.77,0:05:07.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you can think of it as\Nmy capability as a State Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.76,0:05:11.31,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,You finally switched to a northern type?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.31,0:05:12.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you've got some changes, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.91,0:05:17.62,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,This suits me the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:23.63,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Light-weight combat automail, M-1910!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.63,0:05:26.93,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What?! The tip of your nails are reinforced!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.93,0:05:29.13,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it's made out of diamond?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.51,0:05:34.92,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. It's a Neo M-1910, Mad Bear G!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.60,0:05:39.14,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Want me to equip you with something like this, Ed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.14,0:05:40.44,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.44,0:05:43.69,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,So who is this pretty gal?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:45.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,She's my mechanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.57,0:05:58.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell was that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.46,0:06:00.08,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,It kind of pissed me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.83,0:06:02.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What an ass...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.51,0:06:04.53,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,That's the first time I've actually seen a northern automail!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.53,0:06:06.27,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.27,0:06:07.09,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.75,0:06:09.43,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,Then do you want to look around my workplace?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.43,0:06:11.10,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Yes, I'd love to!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.10,0:06:12.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.18,0:06:13.26,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.26,0:06:14.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.96,0:06:18.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get too carried away and walk around all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.88,0:06:22.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of dangerous around here. In a lot of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.71,0:06:25.48,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha. I won't. Thanks for the warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.11,0:06:28.11,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for allowing me to look around!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.43,0:06:30.66,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,This one right here is pretty rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.66,0:06:33.83,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! This is amazing! Isn't this a Crocodile?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.83,0:06:35.33,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.26,0:06:35.98,Default-alt,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx93}She's so spirited about her work, just like how her parents were.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.37,0:06:37.67,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,The thing really setting this apart from others is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.67,0:06:40.94,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx97}...it was designed with the material's expansion rate in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.50,0:06:44.38,Default-alt,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Well, since your limbs are good to go...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.11,0:06:47.63,Default-alt,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,...let's get down to business...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.08,0:06:50.63,Default-alt,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,...Mr. Fullmetal Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:54.64,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.19,0:06:57.87,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...why can't {\i1}I{\i0\fscx30} {\r} be let out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.23,0:06:59.91,Default,Zan,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kimblee's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.26,0:07:04.11,Default,Jel,0000,0000,0000,,We've been told to only release the Fullmetal Alchemist for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.55,0:07:07.25,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee's men...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.73,0:07:10.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,They thought this through, not letting us work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.49,0:07:16.87,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,They've also taken the effort to bring Winry here to show us that she's in their hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.08,0:07:21.37,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that shows how cautious they are about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.14,0:07:25.21,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I can't rush this. I have to wait for the right chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.52,0:07:31.13,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,The advance unit only brought enough food for three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.84,0:07:33.85,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,It's already been a week since they left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.85,0:07:35.02,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,They could be on the verge of starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.37,0:07:37.14,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also worried about their sanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.56,0:07:39.79,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,Being in complete darkness for an entire week is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.82,0:07:42.65,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Let us put our trust in their minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.36,0:07:48.15,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,General, there's no knowing what could happen down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.85,0:07:53.28,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't return in twenty-four hours, please seal this entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.22,0:07:56.28,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.59,0:08:04.87,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Since you're all here, I have something to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.87,0:08:08.55,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,The murder of Lieutenant General Raven was my decision and act, alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.26,0:08:13.05,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You all didn't see or hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.46,0:08:17.81,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,If word gets out, blame everything on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.97,0:08:20.06,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.94,0:08:36.66,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.34,0:08:49.17,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Looks like things are starting to get hectic up north.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.17,0:08:52.92,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We're going to have to start taking the initiative from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.35,0:08:55.43,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Briggs is staffed with men well-versed in defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.18,0:09:00.18,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Only one who excels in both offense and defense can snatch a victory by making the first move.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.68,0:09:06.72,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx92}Which is why Madam Olivier believes that working with the\NEastern Army, well-versed in offensive tactics, is the best option.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.79,0:09:10.82,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor to be selected as a partner for her tag team.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:11.94,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,I think you have it wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.43,0:09:18.40,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,She said she just wants the power of the Eastern Army, and she'd rather you take a hike.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.86,0:09:20.03,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.39,0:09:28.11,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you this, though. What if I sold this information to the Führer President for my own gain?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.11,0:09:32.72,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,"Impossible. Mustang wouldn't do that," so she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.33,0:09:35.47,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be 35,000 cenz.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.93,0:09:39.08,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.45,0:09:43.95,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Madam, who are you exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.81,0:09:49.25,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Just a florist who's worked with the Armstrongs for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.18,0:10:04.87,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hughes, it seems the people who truly understand and support you are the ones who fought beside you in a war.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.51,0:10:06.39,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.12,0:10:10.43,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What to do with these flowers...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.36,0:10:09.37,Default-alt,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.37,0:10:10.43,Default-alt,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,What a weirdo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.43,0:10:11.88,Default-alt,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, god! He's looking this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.96,0:10:17.70,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This is horrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.41,0:10:21.29,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same as Smith's arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.59,0:10:23.75,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Even metal has been cut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.75,0:10:26.35,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Stay on your toes. The enemy may still be around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.00,0:10:36.36,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:41.90,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.90,0:10:43.33,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.43,0:10:45.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,L-Lieutenant Henshel?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.31,0:10:49.92,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,Thank god you're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.92,0:10:51.23,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,Is it just the two of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.23,0:10:51.93,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,What about the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.08,0:10:55.73,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,E-Everyone else is in... p-pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.05,0:10:59.94,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We... We have to get out of here quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.94,0:11:01.23,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That thing will come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.23,0:11:01.98,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,"That thing"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.22,0:11:05.41,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't turn on the lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.41,0:11:07.66,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The shadow... The shadow will come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.75,0:11:07.65,Default-alt,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.66,0:11:08.27,Default-alt,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.91,0:11:12.81,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Get a hold of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.79,0:11:14.77,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The shadow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.70,0:11:20.87,Default,Hen,0000,0000,0000,,Can you stand?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.87,0:11:21.53,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.86,0:11:23.83,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Carry as many men as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.14,0:11:29.58,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for visiting so late at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.44,0:11:33.08,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I've come to deliver an urgent document to the Führer President.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.08,0:11:36.21,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.21,0:11:38.27,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,He's not at home right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.27,0:11:41.55,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like him to look through these by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.55,0:11:45.45,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,By tomorrow, right? I'll let him know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.45,0:11:47.14,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very mu-
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.63,0:11:51.85,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,You were still awake, Selim?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.85,0:11:56.52,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I heard the door open,\Nso I thought Father might have returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.22,0:11:59.40,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,This is Lieutenant Hawkeye.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.85,0:12:01.99,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening, Miss Hawkeye.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.30,0:12:03.53,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.53,0:12:05.94,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,Do you always work such late hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.94,0:12:09.00,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I've come to deliver a document to your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.37,0:12:12.88,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for waking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.37,0:12:19.63,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Selim. You must sleep now, or you'll have a difficult time waking up tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.63,0:12:20.29,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.87,0:12:25.87,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,He seems like a bright boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.33,0:12:30.60,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we're very proud of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.60,0:12:35.31,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,You could call me an indulgent mother if he were my real child, but since he's an orphan, I can boast all I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.86,0:12:42.05,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he's distantly related to my husband, so it could be his blood that made him so wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.31,0:12:45.16,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,He's not related to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.16,0:12:46.06,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.26,0:13:00.55,Default,Haw,0000,0000,0000,,According to the Colonel, King Bradley was raised as a test subject since he was an infant and has no blood relatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.25,0:13:03.03,Default,Haw,0000,0000,0000,,He shouldn't have any distant relatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.60,0:13:05.92,Default,Haw,0000,0000,0000,,And that feeling I sensed earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.30,0:13:07.30,Default,Haw,0000,0000,0000,,Just who is that boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.30,0:13:09.01,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, did you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.02,0:13:14.38,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that mother of mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.38,0:13:15.94,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,She just loves to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.50,0:13:20.35,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I sensed a hint of bloodlust earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.10,0:13:22.43,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I've felt the same sensation before...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.89,0:13:25.45,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,And I just remembered where it was from.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.89,0:13:29.95,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same sensation I felt when a Homunculus by the name of Gluttony snuck up on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.30,0:13:32.95,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Selim Bradley...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.83,0:13:35.71,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Just what are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.28,0:13:42.36,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,You have quite the nerve to ask me that in this situation, Lieutenant Hawkeye.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.63,0:13:47.26,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,It's also smart of you not to pull out your gun, which you're so skilled with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.12,0:13:50.14,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,You can't defeat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.57,0:13:54.05,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Are you also a Homunculus, like Gluttony?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.15,0:13:59.40,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,No, I sense a power that can hardly be compared to that of Gluttony's.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.63,0:14:05.36,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be offended if you put me on the same level as him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.37,0:14:11.45,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Pride. The First Homunculus.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.21,0:14:23.71,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,The First Homunculus, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.17,0:14:25.83,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.83,0:14:27.32,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly as the words mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.59,0:14:32.27,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,So you're planning on gathering as much information as you can, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.27,0:14:34.35,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,You're really a brave one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.86,0:14:37.99,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say you join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.39,0:14:39.43,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Join you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.97,0:14:41.52,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,You just want another pawn, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.52,0:14:44.31,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.94,0:14:45.53,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.38,0:14:53.94,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Will you cut the empty threats already?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.90,0:14:57.37,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,There's no benefit in killing a hostage, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.67,0:15:01.46,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed you saw through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.34,0:15:04.96,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,However, Lieutenant Hawkeye...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.27,0:15:11.04,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,I'll always be watching you from your shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.63,0:15:23.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Work?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.69,0:15:27.19,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, as a State Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.36,0:15:32.15,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,You have three tasks from the Führer President.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.15,0:15:36.65,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Your first task is to search for Scar. All you have to do is find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.65,0:15:38.95,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take care of him after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.95,0:15:45.01,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Your second task is to look for Doctor Marcoh, who is presumed to be escaping alongside Scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.01,0:15:47.16,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Marcoh is with Scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.16,0:15:50.06,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Just like with your previous task,\Nafter you find him, I'll take care of the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.38,0:15:54.70,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Then, your third task is to carve a bloody crest into Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.54,0:15:57.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Carve a bloody crest?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.58,0:16:00.52,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same as Ishbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.52,0:16:04.31,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Slaughtering humans and carving a symbol of hatred and sorrow into the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.17,0:16:07.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I could...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.91,0:16:18.63,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,You became a dog of the military without the resolve to kill?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.63,0:16:20.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,With the resolve {\i1}not{\i0\fscx30} {\r} to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.51,0:16:23.26,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,With a resolve not to kill...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.73,0:16:27.95,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,That can also be true, if you stick with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.95,0:16:32.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Are you lending them a hand,\Nknowing what those guys are up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.88,0:16:33.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,They're-
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.17,0:16:35.96,Default-alt,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see how the world will change.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.00,0:16:38.48,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Resolve pitted against resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.48,0:16:39.72,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Will clashing against will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.72,0:16:41.08,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Life against life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.08,0:16:42.94,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,And humans against the Homunculi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.94,0:16:47.10,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Who will win? Which will the world choose as the victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.88,0:16:55.20,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,If humans are defeated by Homunculi, those who claim to be an evolved form of them, it's truly a historical moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.50,0:16:58.33,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to live to see that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.33,0:17:01.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you, a human, working with the Homunculi?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.52,0:17:07.15,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Because they'll let me use my alchemy as I please.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.51,0:17:08.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You're insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.42,0:17:12.17,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I know that I'm not normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.17,0:17:18.52,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,But if someone like me survives this,\Nthen it means the world's selected me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.52,0:17:19.93,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,The survivors...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:22.95,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,It's a battle for existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:26.90,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,How worthwhile.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.43,0:17:30.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can't understand you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.24,0:17:33.57,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.90,0:17:39.20,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I always thought all alchemists were selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.04,0:17:44.79,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Let me try appealing to your selfish side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.29,0:17:49.54,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Here's something you want more than anything in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.37,0:17:53.51,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,If you accept the job, it's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.89,0:17:56.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A philosopher's stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.47,0:18:05.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let me talk it over with Al and Winry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.74,0:18:07.30,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,With Miss Winry, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.05,0:18:10.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't told her anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.51,0:18:15.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever job I may have to do,\NI don't want to lie to her and betray her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.21,0:18:17.65,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.65,0:18:21.53,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be monitoring you, so you don't tell her anything she doesn't need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.87,0:18:30.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Winry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.43,0:18:33.55,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You're currently being kept as a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.50,0:18:37.67,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.01,0:18:39.30,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.20,0:18:40.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.04,0:18:46.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've been instructed by the higher-ups to do my duty as a human weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.46,0:18:50.47,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So I may have to be party to mass murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.47,0:18:51.31,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.31,0:18:53.48,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But can't you just refuse...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.55,0:18:57.42,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so that's why I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.89,0:19:04.91,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,No... I'm being a burden to you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.83,0:19:07.40,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I won't cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.99,0:19:09.16,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.44,0:19:13.17,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just mad at myself for being so happy-go-lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.01,0:19:15.18,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Why is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.71,0:19:19.24,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You two just want to get your bodies back...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.68,0:19:21.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.95,0:19:25.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,They'll give us a philosopher's stone if I help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.04,0:19:26.48,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What? A stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.48,0:19:27.32,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.32,0:19:28.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee has one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.70,0:19:31.08,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but those stones are made of...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.08,0:19:32.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.30,0:19:44.52,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Do whatever you want, geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.52,0:19:45.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.18,0:19:54.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided to take the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.14,0:19:57.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let me look for Scar first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.61,0:19:59.35,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.12,0:20:03.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Scar killed Winry's parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.02,0:20:04.01,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I want to avenge them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.37,0:20:07.72,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Fair enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.72,0:20:10.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll be taking Al with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.61,0:20:14.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Since he's in that state, Scar can't use his destruction techniques on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.59,0:20:16.86,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, how convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.90,0:20:19.61,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really okay, Al?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.12,0:20:26.62,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,A philosopher's stone is made by sacrificing the lives of many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.09,0:20:33.12,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.85,0:20:36.39,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother isn't planning to use it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.92,0:20:42.18,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We're thinking that there may be a way to get\Nour bodies back by using Eastern Alchemy from Xing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.66,0:20:47.50,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,And a little girl who can use\NEastern Alchemy is supposedly with Scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:51.60,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,So he's making it look like he's going after Scar, but his plan is to get in touch with that girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.61,0:20:53.75,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That's my guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.75,0:20:54.71,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.83,0:21:01.11,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'd better think up a good reason, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.11,0:21:02.36,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.75,0:21:17.50,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to head to the location Scar was last sighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.83,0:21:19.01,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.01,0:21:21.09,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, scoot in!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.16,0:21:28.47,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al, scoot over some more!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.41,0:21:32.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what the heck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.18,0:21:36.54,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Winry, please wait at the fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.54,0:21:38.32,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.32,0:21:39.68,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.68,0:21:42.15,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But I just fixed up his automail, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.15,0:21:46.49,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,It would be bad if it stopped working all of a sudden, so I should go along in case maintenance is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.03,0:21:50.48,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,If something were to happen, it would hurt the proud name of the Rockbells!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.89,0:21:56.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You're really into your work, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.03,0:21:57.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You workaholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.20,0:21:58.82,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'm into it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.82,0:22:02.25,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx93}We've been in business since my great-grandfather's generation!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.25,0:22:03.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.51,0:22:04.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You're from a family of machine freaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.18,0:22:02.25,Default-alt,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.76,0:22:04.35,Default-alt,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I'll allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:06.34,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if you call me a machine freak!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.40,0:22:18.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There's no knowing what will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.39,0:22:20.10,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.73,0:22:25.16,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sick of sitting and waiting for something to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.48,0:24:04.59,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,An all-out war between chimeras and humans takes place in a mining town where the piercing wind blows.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.34,0:24:08.21,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let down your guard. Give it your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.63,0:24:12.64,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,What is the strange aftermath brought forth by the fierce battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.55,0:24:17.71,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.71,0:24:21.73,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 38, Clash in Baschool.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.73,0:24:25.61,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Humans let down their guard in their moments of victory.
